race.description: Secure Last Caulfield Cup Tickets Handicap
race.comment: The potent Wiggins-Taylor linkage should be right to the fore again with WOODSTOCK ROCK (3) rating the galloper to beat. Forgive the latest at Thangool from a wide barrier under an apprentice and he was good winning here prior. Has a high cruising speed and can bounce back. LETS DANCE JANDY (6) is third-up off narrow defeats and raced favourite at Dalby last time. The extra journey is a plus now and he rates among the main chances. PRETTY SLICK (2) runs along and was tracking well before a plainer effort at Emerald in stronger grade. Has to run out the longer sprint but keeps Butler and he will give her every chance. CINDERELLA MAN (5) was much better last time at Gladstone in Open grade and has a low barrier and handy 3kg claim. Shouldn't be underestimated.
